title: Tourism Australia , Garuda Indonesia embark on joint marketing campaignTravelandtourworld.com
text:
Tourism Australia, Garuda Indonesia embark on joint marketing campaign Published  
Marking a milestone in the longstanding partnership, Tourism Australia and Garuda Indonesia have embarked on a joint marketing campaign. The multi-channel campaign focuses on showcasing new and exciting Australian holiday experiences to Indonesian travellers, encouraging first-time and return visits with Garuda to the airline’s key gateway cities, Perth, Melbourne and Sydney.
Australia was the featured destination at the Garuda Travel Fairs in Jakarta and
Surabaya which was launched at the end of September. Results from the Jakarta fare indicate a 70 per cent increase in bookings to Australia over the same travel fare in 2014.
Indonesia is currently Australia’s twelfth largest inbound market for visitor arrivals.
There were 151,400 visitors from Indonesia, an increase of 1.7 per cent relative to the previous year. For the 12 months to August 2015.
 
Source:-Tourism Australia
